en_1392570_0	The Elections Secretariat says that twenty independent parties have placed deposits with regard to the upcoming Western and Southern Provincial Council Elections.
en_1392570_1	Additional Elections Commissioner R.M.A.L. Rathnayake said that ten independent parties placed their deposits on Friday alone. He further said that fifteen independent parties in the Colombo, Gampaha and Kalutara districts in the Western Province have placed deposits during two days.
en_1392570_2	Additional Elections Commissioner R.M.A.L. Rathnayake said that eight independent parties have placed deposits for Colombo district, three for Gampaha district and four for Kalutara district.
en_1392570_3	Five independent parties  have placed deposits for Galle and Matara districts in the Southern Province: however no parties from the Hambantota district have deposited yet.
en_1392570_4	The Elections Secretariat noted that the closing date for placing deposits  will end by 12 noon on February 5.
en_1392570_5	Meanwhile, handing over  of nominations from the Western and Southern Provinces commenced on January 30.
en_1392570_6	The deadline will close by 12 noon on February6.
